article.headline: Houston 64, Marist 58
article.story: SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Brockeith Pane scored 15 points, including a late 3-pointer that put Houston ahead for good, and the Cougars beat Marist 64-58 on Friday in the O'Reilly Auto Parts Puerto Rico Tip-Off. Robert McKiver had 17 points and sank three 3-pointers for the Cougars (1-2), who were coming off a 73-72 loss to Virginia Commonwealth in the tournament opener on Thursday. Jay Gavin went 4-for-8 from 3-point range and scored 16 points to lead the Red Foxes (1-2). Houston led 31-26 at halftime, but the lead changed hands eight times in the second half. Pane then broke a 52-all tie with a 3-pointer with 3:18 left and the Cougars led the rest of the way. Ryan Stilphen scored for Marist before McKiver hit a 3-pointer from the top of the key to stretch Houston's lead to 58-54. McKiver went 4-for-4 from the free-throw line in the final minute to help Houston hang on. Dion Dowell had seven points and 12 rebounds for the Cougars.
